block.translation:
“Choose not Hjorvarth,nor sons of his,

Nor the wives so fairof the famous chief;

Ask not the bridesthat the prince's are;

Fair let us dealin friendly wise.”

block.original:
“Hǫfum erfiþi,etki eyrindi,

mara þraut ōraā meginfjalli;

urþum sīþanSǣmorn vaþa;

þā vas oss synjatSvafnis dōttur,

hringum gø̄ddrar,es hafa vildum.”

Hjǫrvarþr ok Sigrlinn āttu son mikinn ok vænan; hann var þǫgull, ekki nafn festiz viþ hann.

Hann sat ā haugi, hann sā rīþa valkyrjur nīu, ok var ein gǫfugligust;

